Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund Form D
The Alabama-based Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund, L.P. submitted D Form about $18.63 million offering. The date of first sale was 2014-01-01. The Limited Partnership raised $18.63 million. The offering is still open. The total offering amount was $18.63 million. The offering filing was filed on 2015-10-15. Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund, L.P.’s clarification was: The General Partner receives customary management fees as provided in the Issuer’s offering documents.. 
 Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund is based in Alabama. The company’s business is Pooled Investment Fund. The form D was filed by Richard Fradin Principal of the General Partner. The company was incorporated in 2013. The filler’s address is: Rail-Splitter Capital Management, Llc, 303 West Madison Street, Suite 1325, Chicago, Il, Illinois, 60606. — Rail-Splitter Capital Management, Llc is the related person in the form and it has address: 303 West Madison Street, Suite 1325, Chicago, Il, Illinois, 60606. Link to Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund Filing: 000091957415007404.
Analysis of Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund Offering
On average, startups in the Pooled Investment Fund sector, sell 37.80% pooled investment interest. Rail-Splitter Dynamic Growth Fund sold 100.00% of the offering. The average investment offering size is $24.76 million for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund industry sector. The total amount raised is 24.76% smaller than the average for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund sector. 

